Module edu.wgu.qam2schedulingapp
Package edu.wgu.qam2schedulingapp.controller

Class ReportController

java.lang.Object
edu.wgu.qam2schedulingapp.controller.ReportController
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class ReportController extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
This class is the controller for the Report view of the scheduling app. It handles the user interactions with the Report interface, manages the process of fetching appointments data and presenting the reports.
Author:
Parham Modirniya

  • Method Details

    • initialize

      public void initialize(URL url, ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
      Initializes the ReportController. This method is called after the FXMLLoader has completely loaded the FXML. It initializes the reports components and fetches the initial data.
      Specified by:
      initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
      Parameters:
      url - A location used to resolve relative paths for the root object, or null.
      resourceBundle - The resources used to localize the root object, or null.

    • onTargetContactChange

      public void onTargetContactChange()
      Updates the report according to the selected contact. It fetches the appointments data by the selected contact and updates the table.

    • onTargetMonthChange

      public void onTargetMonthChange()
      Updates the report according to the selected month. It fetches the appointments data by the selected type and month if the type is selected, and updates the table.

    • onTargetTypeChange

      public void onTargetTypeChange()
      Updates the report according to the selected type. It fetches the appointments data by the selected type and month if the month is selected, and updates the table.

    • onTargetYearChange

      public void onTargetYearChange()
      Updates the report according to the selected year. It fetches the appointments data by the selected user and year if the user is selected, and updates the table.

    • onTargetUserChange

      public void onTargetUserChange()
      Updates the report according to the selected user. It fetches the appointments data by the selected user and year if the year is selected, and updates the table.

    • navigateToHome

      public void navigateToHome()
      This method is used to navigate back to the home screen of the application. It closes the current stage (window) which is assumed to be the 'Report' stage. The method should be triggered by an action event, typically a button click.
